  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      It is estimated that in the United States there are approximately 8 million individuals with
      moderate to severe chronic kidney disease (CKD), not on dialysis. Volume expansion plays an
      important role in the pathogenesis of hypertension in patients with CKD. For this pilot
      study, the investigators hypothesize that administration of chlorthalidone among patients
      with moderate to severe CKD will improve blood pressure (BP).
    </textblock>
